## Overview

This guide explains the complete onboarding workflow for Semify's REST APIs: obtain a token, create and manage accounts and campaigns, attach service plans, estimate keyword budgets and manage keywords, store credentials securely, retrieve reports, and follow best practices for a robust integration.

---

## Authentication

All API interactions use JWT Bearer tokens.

### Login

- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/authentication/login`  
- Headers: `Content-Type: application/json`  
- Request:
```json
{
  "username": "your_api_username",
  "password": "your_api_password"
}
```
- Sample response:
```json
{
  "error": false,
  "data": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
  "token_exp": 1640995200,
  "message": "Bearer token created and it expires in 60 minutes"
}
```
Note: Tokens expire after 60 minutes; re-authenticate to refresh.

### Using the Token

Include the Bearer token in all requests:
```
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json
```

---

## Account Management (Accounts v2)

### Create Account

- Endpoint: `POST /api/v2/accounts`  
- Required fields: account_name, phone, email, first_name, last_name, address_1, city, state, postal, country, website_url, external_account_identifier  
- Optional: address_2, external_account_manager, external_campaign_manager, attributes

Request example:
```json
{
  "account_name": "Acme Business Solutions",
  "phone": "555-123-4567",
  "email": "contact@acmebusiness.com",
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "address_1": "123 Main Street",
  "address_2": "Suite 100",
  "city": "Anytown",
  "state": "CA",
  "postal": "90210",
  "country": "US",
  "website_url": "https://www.acmebusiness.com",
  "external_account_identifier": "ACME-001",
  "external_account_manager": {
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane.doe@yourcompany.com"
  },
  "external_campaign_manager": {
    "name": "Bob Johnson",
    "email": "bob.johnson@yourcompany.com"
  },
  "attributes": [
    {
      "field_name": "Industry",
      "field_value": "Technology"
    },
    {
      "field_name": "Priority Level",
      "field_value": "High"
    }
  ]
}
```
Sample response:
```json
{
  "data": {
    "campaign_id": "476273",
    "account_id": "424685"
  },
  "messages": ["Account successfully created."],
  "pagination": { "maxRows": 0, "totalPages": 1, "offset": 0, "page": 1, "totalRecords": 1 },
  "error": false
}
```

